var contents = new Array("GENERAL TERMS &amp; POLICIES OF USE \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDefinitions - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUs / We: Means Software Solutions Company - \"Aqua 49 WebStreet Technologies Pvt Ltd\" and \"Synergetic Shipping Solutions LLP\". \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rYou / Subscriber: Means the User of the Vessel or the Company / Organization, using \'DigiMoor X7\' application, as an end-user. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rDigiMoor X7 :  Means complete \"DigiMoor X7 Application\" as developed, marketed and sold by \"Aqua 49 WebStreet Technologies Pvt Ltd\" and \"Synergetic Shipping Solutions LLP\".","1.0.1 GENERAL TERMS & POLICIES OF USE","topics\\1.0.1_GENERAL_TERMS_&_POLICIES_OF_USE.htm","DISCLAIMER \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rUse of DigiMoor X7&nbsp;is at the sole risk of the Subscriber. Neither DigiMoor X7, nor the Agent, nor any lower tier data or service provider shall accept any responsibility for non-supply or for disruption to the DigiMoor X7 service or for the accuracy or reliability of the information as displayed on the Subscriber\'s equipment, nor damages that are caused by the DigiMoor X7&nbsp;or services, whatsoever, and make NO warranty or representation, either express or implied, including the implied warranties or merchantability and fitness for a particular purpose, with respect to the DigiMoor X7&nbsp; and / or services. Furthermore, neither Us, nor the Agent, nor any lower tier data or service provider warrant that DigiMoor X7 will meet the subscriber\'s requirements or that its operation will be uninterrupted or error free. The DigiMoor X7&nbsp;is provided \"AS IS\" and the subscriber assumes the entire risk when using it. It is the responsibility of the subscriber to ensure that the Vessel carries all relevant documents as required by the International Conventions and Regulations. The information produced by the DigiMoor X7&nbsp;is for use onboard the Vessel for which this Subscription Agreement is valid and shall not be copied, sold or otherwise distributed for any other purpose.","1.0.2 DISCLAIMER","topics\\1.0.2_DISCLAIMER.htm","COPYRIGHT NOTICE \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe DigiMoor X7 software and all software components therein are protected by Copyright. Engaging in any of the activities listed below is strictly forbidden - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Distribution of any software, components or other files contained in this software package, other than as instructed by Us. \n\r\n\r-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Modification, design copy, de-compilation, decryption, disassembly, reverse engineering or translation of the software. \n\r\n\r-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Removal of proprietary notices, labels or marks from the software or software documentation. \n\r\n\r-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inclusion of this Software, or any component, within any other software or a development environment. ","1.0.3 COPYRIGHT NOTICE","topics\\1.0.3_COPYRIGHT_NOTICE.htm","TERMS OF USE \n\r\n\rBy accessing and using DigiMoor X7 software, you shall be deemed to have accepted the below Terms and conditions in force from time to time.&nbsp; In case you do not accept these terms and conditions in full, you must not access DigiMoor X7 Software and inform us. Unless otherwise stated, the copyright and all other intellectual property rights in DigiMoor X7 Software, including without limitation data, photographs and graphical images, incorporated or used in concomitance with the DigiMoor X7 software are owned by us. The copyright and all other intellectual property rights in the DigiMoor X7 software are owned by us. \n\r\n\rAny access and use of Data extracted from DigiMoor X7 Software other than in accordance with DigiMoor X7 Terms and Conditions is strictly prohibited. Any external third-party website or other links/mention are provided solely for your convenience. We have not reviewed all of these and do not control and is not responsible for these websites or their content or availability. If you decide to access any of these links/mention you do entirely at your own risk.&nbsp;","1.0.4 TERMS OF USE","topics\\1.0.4_TERMS_OF_USE.htm","VERSIONS OF DIGIMOOR X7\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rA user can select any one of the various available versions of the DigiMoor X7 based upon their requirements and their cost-effectiveness\n\r\n\rDigiMoor X7 (Single User): - Basic version of DigiMoor X7. Best suited for single Crew use, accessing only 1 PC. \n\r\n\rDigiMoor X7 (Network Version): - In addition to the Single User Version this version incorporates the Server-Client relationship spectrum. This Version contains multi-user access and consists of various additional features such as, \n\r  Simultaneous   access from multiple computers at any given time.   Facilitates the   locking of records as to prevent against any accidental or intentional loss of   entered data thereby providing an additional security layer.   Secure access for   each user from anywhere on the Network. \n\r\n\r\n\rDigiMoor X7 (Online Version): - This version is for Shore-based management Personnel to access their Vessel/Fleet\'s records at any given time and also helps in building up numerous analytical statistics for their entire fleet.","1.0.5 VERSIONS","topics\\1.0.5_VERSIONS.htm","LOGIN URL \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rURL of the site work according to the company name and the User permission.\n\r\n\rA. Format of the URL    :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; https://companyname.mooringplan.com \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  \n\r\n\rwhere \"Company name\" represent the Subdomain name of the client using the DigimoorX7 Online version. And mooringplan.com is the main domain of the application.\n\r\n\rB. Login page:\n\r\n\rLogin page is where user login with the Username and password as provided to them as per the requirement as Admin or As User\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1. ADMIN USER : The main User who has the interface right of all Vessel and permission to change all the data.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2. USER : Here user can see only the vessel or vessels asigned to him/her for the data input.\n\r\n\rC. PASSWORD CHANGE : \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTo reset the password user can request by clicking on the Reset Password link. enter the login credential username provided (email). Click on the Email Link.\n\r\n\rAfter clicking on the button, a link to reset the password id shared on te user email. Open the link follow the onscreen procedure.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;","1.0.6 LOGIN","topics\\1.0.6_LOGIN.htm","ABOUT DIGIMOOR X7\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\'DigiMoor X7, an intelligent, \'easy to install - operate software\', for efficient recordkeeping management of mooring loose gear on board Ships and its monitoring &amp; analysis ashore. \n\r\n\rDigiMoor X7 complies to the requirements of \"Mooring Equipment Guidelines 4 (MEG 4)\".\n\r\n\rThe software includes MSMP and LMP e-manuals and helps Ships in recordkeeping of Mooring ropes, rope tails and loose equipment lifecycle data for - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mooring operations - Records complete details of Berth, environmental conditions, running hours &amp; leads of ropes etc for each Port. \n\r\n\r2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inspections of Ropes, Rope Tails and loose equipment. \n\r\n\r3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ropes, rope tails and loose equipment details.\n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lifecycle records of ropes, rope tails and loose equipment from receipt to disposal\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIn addition, it incorporates an approx. calculator for checking factor of safety for mooring ropes at each berth as per the load they are expected to experience at the input environmental conditions. ","1.0 ABOUT","topics\\1.0_ABOUT.htm","NOTIFICATION\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; See the Subsections of the File\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","2.0 NOTIFICATION","topics\\2.0_NOTIFICATION.htm","\n\r\n\rNOTIFICATION\n\r\n\rThe DigiMoor X7 software incorporates a state-of-the-art alerting systems with its Audio/Visual notifications. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThese notifications are generated for following functions - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inventory\n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When count of minimum required ropes is below desired.\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When count of minimum required rope tails is below desired.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inspection - Inspection due dates depends on the inspection criteria set by the Company, which may change time to time. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For Lines, Rope Tail &amp; Loose Equipment - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 7 days before inspection due date.\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inspection due date.\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inspection overdue.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Discard - Discard criteria depends on the inspection / discard criteria set by the Company, which may change time to time. \n\r\n\r4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For&nbsp;Lines &amp; Rope Tail - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pre-Warning - When inspection rating reaches rating \'6\'.\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Discard warning - When inspection rating reaches rating \'7\'. \n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum running hours approaching (20% less than maximum running hours). \n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum running hours exceeded. \n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum allowable time approaching (12 months before maximum allowed time). \n\r\n\rf)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum allowable time exceeded. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For Loose Equipment - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum allowable time approaching (12 months before maximum allowed time). \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maximum allowable time exceeded. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; End to End\n\r\n\rFor Lines / Rope - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; End to End Approaching (1 month before End to End due date)\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; End to End Due \n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; End to End Overdue\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winch Rotation \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For Lines / Rope - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rotation Approaching (1 month before End to End due date)\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rotation Due\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rotation Overdue\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cropping\n\r\n\rFor Lines /&nbsp;&nbsp;Rope - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When rope is cropped above allowable 10% of its entire length.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8.&nbsp;&nbsp; Damaged\n\r\n\rFor Lines , Rope Tail &amp; Loose Equipment - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When any rope is spliced \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splicing\n\r\n\rFor&nbsp; Lines / Rope - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When any rope is spliced \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 10.&nbsp; Discarded\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For Lines, Rope Tail &amp; Loose Equipment - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When any rope is discarded\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 11.&nbsp; Disposed\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; For Lines , Rope Tail &amp; Loose Equipment - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When any rope is disposed\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rShould any Deviation arise due to any reason, the DigiMoor X7 icon on the Taskbar will turn red in colour and it will automatically generate an alarm as well as the notification displaying there exists a Deviation which has not been acknowledged. DigiMoor X7 generates Audio &amp; Visual Alarms. User has been provided with facility to acknowledge deviations. Facility has also been provided to acknowledge multiple of all Deviations simultaneously. To acknowledge multiple Deviation, select the Deviation that you want to acknowledge using checkbox, then click on Acknowledge button to Acknowledge all selected values.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rMoving pages - There are arrows displayed on top centre of the page to move the pages (previous / next symbols). Single arrow denotes single page shift, double arrow donates first and last page respectively. ","2.1 NOTIFICATIONS","topics\\2.1_NOTIFICATIONS.htm","NOTIFICATION - SHIP AND OFFICE COMMENTS\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rShip Comments - Every notification has a facility to be commented upon. A simple link to \'Add Comment\' is displayed besides each notification, which when clicked opens another window to comment. \n\r\n\rTo write comment, press \'Add Comment\' button, write text in the text box and then press \'Save\' button. \n\r\n\rMultiple comments can be written for each notification. \n\r\n\rAll ship comments will be saved in the list. \n\r\n\rAll ship comments get exported to the office via the export file. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rOffice Comments - Every notification has a facility to view Office Comments. Office end comments are imported via the import file from the office. \n\r\n\rAll Unread Office Comments are highlighted on top of the page. \n\r\n\rWhen clicked on the office comment link, it automatically turns \'read\' from \'unread\' mode. \n\r\n\rOffice comments are non-editable from Shipboard version.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","2.2 SHIP AND OFFICE COMMENTS","topics\\2.2_SHIP_AND_OFFICE_COMMENTS.htm","NOTIFICATION - ACKNOWLEDGE&nbsp;\n\r\n\rEach notification should be acknowledged before exporting data to the office. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To Acknowledge Notification - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp; Click on the checkbox besides the notification.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp; Press the \'Acknowledge\' button on top left side. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After the notification is acknowledged, it will turn to black colour and then move in Archives. \n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp; You may select all notifications and acknowledge together. To do this, click on the topmost checkbox, which will automatically select all notifications on default page and then click the \'Acknowledge\' button on top left side. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","2.3 ACKNOWLEDGE","topics\\2.3_ACKNOWLEDGE.htm","ARCHIVES\n\r\n\rThe unacknowledged notifications are displayed on the default screen. To check any previous acknowledged notifications, click on \'Archives\' button &amp; select \'From\' &amp; \'To\' Date from the calendar. To return to default page, press \'Go Back\' button on the extreme right side of the page.\n\r\n\r                                            &nbsp;\n\r\n\r                                            ","2.4 ARCHIVES","topics\\2.4_ARCHIVES.htm","MOORING MANUAL\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rMooring manual section incorporates all the \'Manual Text, images and attachments\' part of the software and is displayed as \'e-manual\'. These may contain MSMP (Mooring System Management Plan), LMP (Line Management Plan) and Training Content. \n\r\n\rEach Manual may be divided into various sections and subsections. \n\r\n\rTo access these section, click on the desired menu name from the left sidebar submenu, and the relevant section will appear in the right side besides. \n\r\n\r                       \n\r\n\rThe manuals text are \'Read Only\' and contains four sections - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; General Data         \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This section is applicable to \'All Ships of the Company\' and contains the e-manuals applicable to the MSMP (Mooring System Management Plan), LMP&nbsp; (Line&nbsp; Management Plan) and Training Content. \n\r\n\rFor easy scrolling, \'Previous\' and \'Next\' buttons are provided to the User, which will take the user to previous or next section / subsection as listed in the manual.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;                             \n\r\n\r&nbsp;b. Ship Specific Data                             \n\r\n\rThis section is \'Ship-specific\' which is applicable to individual Ship only, and contains ship-specific sections from the manual. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;                              \n\r\n\r                             \n\r\n\r&nbsp;c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ship Specific Attachments                             \n\r\n\rThis section is available to attach the Ship specific documents. The list of minimum required attachments may be obtained from your Company\'s office. \n\r\n\rThe attachments may either be shared by your office or may be attached by the Ship staff themselves. \n\r\n\rAttachments that are shared by the office will be received in a folder, which is to be directly imported via \'Import Text\' and \'Import Attachment\' from the \'Import\' sub-menu under \'Administration\' menu. \n\r\n\rThe attachments which are shared by the office appear in the list in relevant section only and is not possible to be deleted. To delete these, please request your office to delete the same from their Office-end version and reshare the \'Import Text\' file, which should be imported in the Ship via&nbsp; Import system. \n\r\n\rAttachments can be only of following types - \n\r\n\rPdf, MS Word, MS Excel and Images. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Revisions\n\r\n\rThis section is applicable to \'All Ships of the Company\' and lists the various revision numbers of the sections and subsections. \n\r\n\rThe revision numbers are section specific only. The revision numbers are automatically generated via the office-end and gets updated with the latest \'Import Text\' file. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rOther functions of the Mooring Manual Section include - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Search - \n\r\n\rThe Search option may be utilized to search any text from the complete manual. \n\r\n\rTo Search, type the desired text eg: LDBF and press the \'Search\' button besides, this will open a page with the relevant results from each section where this text keyword was located. Now click on the desired section to view the excerpt of the text containing the Search term. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PDF&nbsp; - \n\r\n\rThe PDF download option is available for each page of the manual. \n\r\n\rOn pressing the PDF button, it will create and download the section which is currently open on the screen. \n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Print - \n\r\n\rTo print text of a particular section, create &amp; download its pdf via the above PDF download procedure. The option to print shall now appear within the PDF file.","3.0 MOORING MANUAL","topics\\3.0_MOORING_MANUAL.htm","L M P R (Line Management Plan Register) &nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; See Sub Sections of the File for more Information.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.0 LINE MANAGEMENT PLAN REGISTER","topics\\4.0_LINE_MANAGEMENT_PLAN_REGISTER.htm","Mooring Operation Records\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This section is to record all available information after a mooring operation is conducted. It is required that \'All\' mooring operations where any mooring ropes were used, shall be recorded in this section. The details to fill this form are given below :\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r  Adding new Mooring Operation   - To add a new mooring operation, click on \'LMPR\' menu, then click on   \'Mooring Operations\' submenu which will open Mooring operation page. On this   page, click on \'Add Mooring Operation\' button which will open a form to fill   all details.\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r  Mooring   Operation Records form fields - \n\r\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Port Name: Type the Port name which will search the list of all ports and suggest the available names in the list below, choose the desired name to fill this field. \n\r\n\rIn case the desired Port name is not available in this list, search for \'Other\' and click to select \'Other\' from the list. On selection of \'Other\', a text field will open underneath this field, please insert the desired name of the Port here. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date &amp; Time for All Fast : Insert the Logbook date and time for mooring \'All Fast\'. To select the date, click on the calendar icon besides, which will open a calendar, click to choose the desired date. \n\r\n\rTo enter time, choose hours from the first time dropdown and minutes from the second time dropdown. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date &amp; Time for Cast Fast : Insert the Logbook date and time for mooring \'All Cast Off\'. To select the date, click on the calendar icon besides, which will open a calendar, click to choose the desired date. \n\r\n\rTo enter time, choose hours from the first time dropdown and minutes from the second time dropdown. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winches used for the full period : A list of all available winches with ropes warped on them will appear here. Click the checkbox to select all used winches / ropes &amp; rope tails. Then select the direction and lead for each rope. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rIn case a Winch / Rope is not used for the full period from \'All Fast\' to \'Cast Off\', an option is given to \'Add More\'. To use this option, follow below steps - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; i)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure winches / ropes not used for complete operations shall be unchecked from the main topmost section of winches. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Press \'Add More\' button, which will open a subsection underneath containing list of winches / ropes which are unchecked on top. It also displays selector of date &amp; time from - to, which should be filled for the time the selected winches / ropes were used. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; iii)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The \'Add More\' button is equipped to create 4 such additional timing subsections. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Facility Name : This field automatically lists the available facilities upon selection of the first field \'Port Name\'. \n\r\n\rIn case the \'Port Name\' is selected as \'Other\', then a blank text field will appear here instead of the available list of facilities. Please type the desired name of the facility. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Berth Name / Number : Text field to insert Berth Name or Number. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Berth Type : Dropdown field with available selections from various values, select the value applicable to the specific berth where the Ship was berthed. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type of Mooring : Dropdown field with available selections from various values, select the value applicable to the specific berth where the Ship was berthed.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Drafts Arrival / Departure Fwd and Aft : Drafts of the Vessel on Arrival and Departure forward and aft in metres, respectively. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Depth at Berth : Field to insert the depth at berth in metres. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Berthing Side : Selection from dropdown - Port or Stbd. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Vessel Condition : Dropdown field with available selections from various values, select the value applicable to the specific berth where the Ship was berthed. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ship access : Dropdown field with available selections from various values, select the value applicable to the specific berth where the Ship was berthed. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Range of Tide : Field to insert the maximum tidal range in metres.&nbsp; \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Avg Wind Direction : Dropdown to select from 1 to 7, as per the average direction of wind at the berth. A diagram is given besides displaying the direction selection to be used. This direction is relative to the bow of the Vessel in clockwise direction. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Avg Wind Speed : Average speed of winds in knots. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Any Squall / Gusts experienced : Dropdown option to select Yes or No. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Current Speed : Average speed of current in knots.\n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Berth exposed to Sea / Swell : Dropdown option to select Yes or No. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Surging observed : Dropdown option to select Yes or No. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Any affect of passing traffic : Dropdown option to select Yes or No. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ship was continuously in contact with fender: Dropdown option to select Yes or No. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Master\'s Notes for this Port Call : Text box to enter Master\'s observations of the Port. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Was any rope damaged : Dropdown option to select Yes or No. \n\r\n\r·&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Recording&nbsp;Line Damage : Any damages to the Lines in the duration of the operation should be recorded here itself. However, in case it is missed, there is an option later also to add/delete damaged ropes in an operation. To add damage lines, follow below steps - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; i)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select \'Yes\' in dropdown in the mooring operation form for the filed - \'Was any&nbsp;line damaged?\'\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the bottom of this page, a new button will appear \'Add Damaged Lines\', click on this button, which will open a popup with form to enter the damaged&nbsp;line details. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;iii)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click on \'Add Damage Line\' button to open this form.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r    Mooring Operation Records List View&nbsp; -   \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r    View Damage LINE: Click on this   button to View the list of lines damaged in this operation. You may add   additional lines from this option. \n\r    View Mooring Op: Click on this   button to View the Mooring Operation details which were stored previously.   \n\r    Delete: Click on this button to   delete any Mooring Op record. Please note once deleted, you will not be able   to retrieve this data. \n\r","4.1 MOORING OPERATION","topics\\4.1_MOORING_OPERATION.htm","TAIL RESIDUAL LAB TEST\n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Rope Residual Lab Test\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rTo add the Rope Tail Residual Strength Test report, which you have received form the testing laboratory, please follow below steps -\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click on \'Add Rope Tail Res Strength Test\' button to make an entry, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below -\n\r\n\rSelect Rope: Dropdown lists Rope Tail Certificate numbers to be selected as desired\n\r\n\rRope Type: View only field, automatically populates on selection of Select Rope field. \n\r\n\rManufacturer: View only field, automatically populates on selection of Select Rope field. \n\r\n\rRope Location: View only field, automatically populates on selection of Select Rope field.\n\r\n\rLab Test Date: Select the Lab test date as mentioned in the lab testing report. \n\r\n\rMonths in Service: View only field, displayed in units as \'Months\', calculated as (Lab Test Date - Installed Date).\n\r\n\rRunning Hours in Service: View only field, Current running hours as being recorded automatically. &nbsp;\n\r\n\rResidual Strength as per Test Report (Percentage): Enter percentage as mentioned in the lab test report (Max 100%). \n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter your remarks, if any.\n\r\n\rReset: Pressing this button resets the form entries you made, after reset, reselect the Rope to fill the form again.\n\r\n\rSave: After entering all information in the form, click on Save button to save in records. \n\r\n\rCancel: Pressing this button will take you back to the list. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.10 TAIL RESIDUAL LAB TEST","topics\\4.10_TAIL_RESIDUAL_LAB_TEST.htm","MOORING&nbsp;LINE INSPECTION\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This option is available to list and create Mooring&nbsp;Lines inspection details. All past inspections are listed on this page. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To view any past year data, click on the Year dropdown and press \'Search\' button besides to list past year data. By default the current year dropdown is selected. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New Inspection: Click on this button to add a new inspection of Mooring Lines.&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r  Mooring&nbsp;Line Inspection View -   \n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Lines &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Lines Inspection &gt; Add Inspection option. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe options on this page are listed below with respective details - \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rInspection Date: Calendar to choose the actual date when the selected&nbsp;Lines were inspected. \n\r\n\rInspection By: Generally Name &amp; Rank of the person inspecting to be inserted here.\n\r\n\rInspection Guidance: Click on this button to download Infographic guidance pdf on the ratings to be marked during an inspection, basis rope conditions. \n\r\n\rDownload Inspection Excel Sheet: Click this button to download an automatically generated excel sheet containing all available&nbsp;Lines onboard. This can be printed and carried along during inspection for ease of use. \n\r\n\rCheckbox: Checkbox besides each rope should be clicked to enter the inspection data. Only&nbsp;Lines which are checked would be stored as inspected. \n\r\n\rZone A: Chock or Fairlead Contact area zone. The result of inspection of the rope which remains in this zone to be noted in the available fields below this section. \n\r\n\rZone B: Winch Drum Contact area zone. The result of inspection of the rope which remains in this zone to be noted in the available fields below this section. \n\r\n\rExternal: Compulsory field, External rating of the rope basis its condition. Please follow the inspection guidance as above. The ratings are selectable from 1 to 7, 1 being the best condition and 7 worst condition which should be discarded. \n\r\n\rInternal: Compulsory field, Internal rating of the rope basis its condition. Please follow the inspection guidance as above. The ratings are selectable from 1 to 7, 1 being the best condition and 7 worst condition which should be discarded. \n\r\n\rPhoto 1 &amp; Photo 2: Non-Compulsory field. Facility has been provided to attach photographs (maximum 2) per rope. The maximum size of photo attachment is 200 kbs only. \n\r\n\rOther fields are as mentioned in the labels. \n\r\n\rSave: After inserting Inspection data, click on Save button to Save. If Save is not clicked, data will not be saved. \n\r\n\rCancel: Click on this button if the user does not want to save the inserted data.","4.2.1 MOORING LINE INSPECTION","topics\\4.2.1_MOORING_LINE_INSPECTION.htm","MOORING&nbsp;LINES DETAILS\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rAll Mooring&nbsp;Lines details shall be listed in this section. \n\r\n\rTo add any new&nbsp;Lines detail, click on \'Add&nbsp;Lines Details\' button on top right side.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r    Mooring&nbsp;Line Details Form View -   \n\r\n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line Details&gt; Add&nbsp;Lines Details. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe options on this page are listed below with respective details - \n\r\n\r\n\r    Rope Type: Dropdown to select one option from the   list.\n\r    Rope Construction: Text field to   enter&nbsp;Line construction details. \n\r    Diameter (mm) : Enter&nbsp;Line   diameter here in millimetres.\n\r    Length (mtrs) : Enter&nbsp;Line   diameter here in metres.\n\r    MBL (T) : Enter&nbsp;Line MBL here   in Tonnes. \n\r    LDBF (T) : Enter&nbsp;Line LDBF   here in Tonnes. \n\r    WLL (T) : Enter&nbsp;Line WLL here   in Tonnes. \n\r    Manufacturer Name: Dropdown to   select one option from the list.\n\r    Certificate Number: Enter   the&nbsp;Line Certificate Number here. \n\r    Received Date: Compulsory field,   Calendar to select date of receipt of the rope. This date can only be a past   date. \n\r    Installed Date: Non-compulsory   field, Calendar to select the installation date. In case the rope is kept as   non-used spare, please leave this field blank.   \n\r    This field is connected to calculation   of discard criteria, hence only apply when the rope is in actual use.   \n\r    Rope Tagging: Dropdown to select   Yes / No. Ropes are ge\n\r    Existing Running Hours: Start   counter of Running hours, generally applicable to used existing ropes being   inserted into the software. Please enter the running hours this rope has   already consumed. \n\r    Remarks: Text box to enter remarks   related to the rope. \n\r    Save: Press Save button to save all data   entered.\n\r","4.2.2 MOORING LINE DETAILS","topics\\4.2.2_MOORING_LINE_DETAILS.htm","ASSIGN&nbsp;LINE TO WINCH\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt; Assign&nbsp;Line to Winch\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe options on this page are listed below with respective details - \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rActive Records: List of Liness assigned to winch currently \n\r\n\rPast Records: Past records of assignment and rotation on winches. \n\r\n\rAssign&nbsp;Line to Winch: Click on this button to assign&nbsp;Line to winch, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Line: Dropdown to select the available lines as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): Select the current outboard end as per your Ship\'s marking.&nbsp;Line ends to be marked with A and B at opposite ends. After reeling on the winch, select the end currently on outboard side. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assigned Date: Selection of date when the&nbsp;line was reeled on the winch. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assign&nbsp;Line to Winch: Dropdown to select the desired Winch number where the selected&nbsp;line is currently reeled. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Line location assign: View only field which appears after selection of the Winch number\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.2.3 ASSIGN LINE TO WINCH","topics\\4.2.3_ASSIGN_LINE_TO_WINCH.htm","LINE END TO END\n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt;&nbsp;Line End to End\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLine&nbsp;End to End: Click on this button to make an entry of&nbsp;Line End to End operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Line: Dropdown to select the available&nbsp;lines as per their certificate numbers. These will list only the&nbsp;lines which are assigned to winch. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): Select the current outboard end as per your Ship\'s marking.&nbsp;Line ends to be marked with A and B at opposite ends. After reeling on the winch, select the end currently on outboard side. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assigned Date: Selection of date when the&nbsp;Line was reeled on the winch. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assign&nbsp;Line to Winch: Dropdown to select the desired Winch number where the selected&nbsp;line is currently reeled. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Line location assign: View only field which appears after selection of the Winch number\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.2.4 LINE END TO END","topics\\4.2.4_LINE_END_TO_END.htm","LINE SPLICING\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt;&nbsp;Line Splicing\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLine&nbsp;Splicing : Click on the \'Add&nbsp;Line Splicing\' button to make an entry of&nbsp;Line Splicing operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Line: Dropdown to select the available&nbsp;lines as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Line winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Line Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splicing Done Date: Calendar to select the date on which splicing was done. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;f)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splicing Method: Text field eg: Hand Splicing, Mechanical splicing etc values may be entered. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; g)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splicing Done by: Dropdown to Select options from \'Shore Assistance\' or \'Onboard. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; h)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Is&nbsp;Line Cropped: Dropdown to Select \'Yes\' or \'No\'. On selection of Yes, following fields will open - \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Cropped Outboard End: Selection of outboard end which was cropped \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Cropped&nbsp;Line Lt: Cropped&nbsp;line length in metres. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Reasons for Cropping: Dropdown list to select one or more reasons for Cropping.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.2.5 LINE SPLICING","topics\\4.2.5_LINE_SPLICING.htm","LINE CROPPING &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt;&nbsp;Line Cropping&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLine&nbsp;Cropping : Click on the \'Add&nbsp;Line Cropping\' button to make an entry of&nbsp;Line Cropping operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Line : Dropdown to select the available lines as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Line winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Line Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cropped Date: Calendar to select the date on which cropping was done. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;f)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cropped Outboard End: Selection of outboard end which was cropped.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; g)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cropped Rope Lt: Cropped&nbsp;line length in metres.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; h)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reasons for Cropping: Dropdown list to select one or more reasons for Cropping.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.2.6 LINE CROPPING","topics\\4.2.6_LINE_CROPPING.htm","LINE DAMAGE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt;&nbsp;Line Damage\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLine&nbsp;Damage : Click on the \'Add Damage Line\' button to make an entry of&nbsp;Line Damage operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Line: Dropdown to select the available lines as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Line winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Line Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Observed: Dropdown to select the operation when damage was located i.e. during \'Inspection\' or \'Mooring operation\'. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;f)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Date: Calendar to select date of damage observed. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; g)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incident Report: Dropdown to select \'Yes\' or \'No\'. Select \'Yes\' if the damage resulted in an incident and report of incident is recorded.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.2.7 LINE DAMAGE","topics\\4.2.7_LINE_DAMAGE.htm","LINE DISCARD&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt;&nbsp;Line Discard\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp; \n\r\n\r&nbsp; \n\r\n\rLine&nbsp; Discard : Click on the \'Add&nbsp;Line Discard\' button to make an entry of&nbsp;Line Discard operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Line : Dropdown to select the available lines as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Line winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Line Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Number of Operation: View only field, lists number of operations this rope has undergone in its life. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; f)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Running Hours: View only field, lists the total running hours this&nbsp;line has undergone in its life.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;g)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date Out of Service: Calendar to select date of Discard or Out of Service\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;h)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reason Out of Service: Dropdown to select reason for discard. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;i)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Observed: Dropdown to select from options of \'Inspection\' or \'Mooring Operation\'. On selection of \'Mooring Operation\', the system shows another dropdown below to select the name of the Operation. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; j)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Reason: Dropdown to select from various available options.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; k)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Location: Dropdown to select from various available options.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.2.8 LINE DISCARD","topics\\4.2.8_LINE_DISCARD.htm","LINE DISPOSAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring&nbsp;Line &gt;&nbsp;Line Disposal\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rLine&nbsp; Disposal : Click on the \'Add&nbsp;Line Disposal\' button to make an entry of&nbsp;Line Disposal operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below -\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Line : Dropdown to select the available lines as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date Out of Service: View only field\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Disposal Port Name: Text field to add name of Port where the&nbsp;line was disposed.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reception Facility Name: Text field to add facility name which received the disposed&nbsp;line in the Port. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Disposal Date: Calendar to select date of disposal. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.2.9 LINE DISPOSAL","topics\\4.2.9_LINE_DISPOSAL.htm","Mooring&nbsp;Line\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; See Sub sections for Details \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.2 MOORING LINE","topics\\4.2_MOORING_LINE.htm","MOORING ROPE TAIL INSPECTION \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis option is available to list and create Mooring rope tail inspection details. All past inspections are listed on this page. \n\r\n\rTo view any past year data, click on the Year dropdown and press \'Search\' button besides to list past year data. By default the current year dropdown is selected. \n\r\n\rNew Inspection: Click on this button to add a new inspection of Mooring Rope Tail. \n\r\n\r-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mooring Rope Tail Inspection View - \n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope &gt; Mooring Rope Tail Inspection &gt; Add New Inspection option. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe options on this page are listed below with respective details - \n\r\n\rInspection Date: Calendar to choose the actual date when the selected rope tails were inspected.\n\r\n\r            Inspection By: Generally                             Name &amp; Rank of the person inspecting to be inserted here. \n\r\n\r           Inspection Guidance:                    Click on this button to download Infographic guidance pdf on the ratings to be marked during an inspection, basis rope conditions. \n\r\n\r                    Download Inspection Excel Sheet:           Click this button to download an automatically generated excel sheet containing all available rope tails onboard. This can be printed and carried along during inspection for ease of use. \n\r\n\r                             Checkbox:                 Checkbox besides each rope tails should be clicked to enter the inspection data. Only rope tails which are checked would be stored as inspected. \n\r\n\r                       External: Compulsory field, External rating of the rope tail basis its condition. Please follow the inspection guidance as above. The ratings are selectable from 1 to 7, 1 being the best condition and 7 worst condition which should be discarded. \n\r\n\r                                        Internal: Compulsory field, Internal rating of the rope tail basis its condition. Please follow the inspection guidance as above. The ratings are selectable from 1 to 7, 1 being the best condition and 7 worst condition which should be discarded. \n\r\n\rPhoto 1 &amp; Photo 2: Non-Compulsory field. Facility has been provided to attach photographs (maximum 2) per rope tail. The maximum size of photo attachment is 200 kbs                                       only. \n\r\n\rOther fields are as mentioned in the labels. \n\r\n\rSave: After inserting Inspection data, click on Save button to Save. If Save is not clicked, data will not be saved. \n\r\n\rCancel: Click on this button if the user does not want to save the inserted data. ","4.3.1 MOORING ROPE TAIL INSPECTION","topics\\4.3.1_MOORING_ROPE_TAIL_INSPECTION.htm","MOORING ROPE TAIL DETAILS\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; All Mooring Rope Tail details shall be listed in this section. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add any new Rope Tail detail, click on \'Add Rope Tail Details\' button on top right side:\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r Mooring Rope Tail Details Form View - \n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope Tail &gt; Mooring Rope Tail Details&gt; Add Rope Tail Details.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe options on this page are listed below with respective details - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rRope Tail Type: Dropdown to select one option from the list.\n\r\n\rRope Tail Construction: Text field to enter rope Tail construction details. \n\r\n\rDiameter (mm) : Enter rope Tail diameter here in millimetres.\n\r\n\rLength (mtrs) : Enter rope Tail diameter here in metres.\n\r\n\rMBL (T) : Enter rope Tail MBL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rLDBF (T) : Enter rope Tail LDBF here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rWLL (T) : Enter rope Tail WLL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Dropdown to select one option from the list.\n\r\n\rCertificate Number: Enter the Rope Tail Certificate Number here. \n\r\n\rReceived Date: Compulsory field, Calendar to select date of receipt of the rope Tail. This date can only be a past date. \n\r\n\rInstalled Date: Non-compulsory field, Calendar to select the installation date. In case the rope Tail is kept as non-used spare, please leave this field blank. \n\r\n\rThis field is connected to calculation of discard criteria, hence only apply when the rope Tail is in actual use. \n\r\n\rRope Tail Tagging: Dropdown to select Yes / No. Rope Tails are ge\n\r\n\rExisting Running Hours: Start counter of Running hours, generally applicable to used existing rope Tails being inserted into the software. Please enter the running hours this rope Tail has already consumed. \n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter remarks related to the rope Tail. \n\r\n\rSave: Press Save button to save all data entered. ","4.3.2 MOORING ROPE TAIL DETAILS","topics\\4.3.2_MOORING_ROPE_TAIL_DETAILS.htm","ASSIGN ROPE TAIL TO WINCH \n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope Tail &gt; Assign Rope Tail to Winch\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rThe options on this page are listed below with respective details -\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rActive Records: List of Rope Tails assigned to winch currently \n\r\n\rPast Records: Past records of assignment and rotation on winches. \n\r\n\rAssign Rope Tail to Winch: Click on this button to assign rope Tail to winch, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Rope Tail: Dropdown to select the available rope Tails as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): Select the current outboard end as per your Ship\'s marking. Rope Tail ends to be marked with A and B at opposite ends. After reeling on the winch, select the end currently on outboard side. \n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assigned Date: Selection of date when the rope Tail was reeled on the winch. \n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assign Rope Tail to Winch: Dropdown to select the desired Winch number where the selected Rope Tail is currently reeled. \n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail location assign: View only field which appears after selection of the Winch number\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.3.3 ASSIGN ROPE TAIL TO WINCH","topics\\4.3.3_ASSIGN_ROPE_TAIL_TO_WINCH.htm","ROPE TAIL SPLICING \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope Tail &gt; Rope Tail Splicing\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rRope Tail Splicing : Click on the \'Add Rope Tail Splicing\' button to make an entry of Rope Tail Splicing operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Rope Tail: Dropdown to select the available rope Tails as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rope Tail winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splicing Done Date: Calendar to select the date on which splicing was done. \n\r\n\rf)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splicing Method: Text field eg: Hand Splicing, Mechanical splicing etc values may be entered. \n\r\n\rg)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Splicing Done by: Dropdown to Select options from \'Shore Assistance\' or \'Onboard.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.3.4 ROPE TAIL SPLICING","topics\\4.3.4_ROPE_TAIL_SPLICING.htm","ROPE TAIL CROPPING \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope Tail &gt; Rope Tail Cropping\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rRope Tail Cropping : Click on the \'Add Rope Tail Cropping\' button to make an entry of Rope Tail Cropping operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below -\n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Rope Tail: Dropdown to select the available rope tails as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cropped Date: Calendar to select the date on which cropping was done. \n\r\n\rf)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cropped Outboard End: Selection of outboard end which was cropped.\n\r\n\rg)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cropped Rope Tail Lt: Cropped rope tail length in metres.\n\r\n\rh)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reasons for Cropping: Dropdown list to select one or more reasons for Cropping.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.3.5 ROPE TAIL CROPPING","topics\\4.3.5_ROPE_TAIL_CROPPING.htm","ROPE TAIL DAMAGE\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope Tail &gt; Rope Tail Damage\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rRope Tail Damage : Click on the \'Add Damage Rope Tail\' button to make an entry of Rope Tail Damage operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Rope Tail: Dropdown to select the available rope tails as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Observed: Dropdown to select the operation when damage was located i.e. during \'Inspection\' or \'Mooring operation\'. \n\r\n\rf)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Date: Calendar to select date of damage observed. \n\r\n\rg)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Incident Report: Dropdown to select \'Yes\' or \'No\'. Select \'Yes\' if the damage resulted in an incident and report of incident is recorded. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.3.6 ROPE TAIL DAMAGE","topics\\4.3.6_ROPE_TAIL_DAMAGE.htm","ROPE TAIL DISCARD\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope Tail &gt; Rope Tail Discard\n\r\n\r            &nbsp;\n\r\n\r            \n\r\n\r            &nbsp;\n\r\n\rRope Tail Discard : Click on the \'Add Rope Tail Discard\' button to make an entry of Rope Tail Discard operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below -\n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Rope Tail: Dropdown to select the available rope tails as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Outboard End in Use (A/B): View only field\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail winch assigned: View only field\n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Tail Location assigned: View only field\n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Number of Operation: View only field, lists number of operations this rope tail has undergone in its life. \n\r\n\rf)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Running Hours: View only field, lists the total running hours this rope tail has undergone in its life.\n\r\n\rg)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date Out of Service: Calendar to select date of Discard or Out of Service\n\r\n\rh)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reason Out of Service: Dropdown to select reason for discard. \n\r\n\ri)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Observed: Dropdown to select from options of \'Inspection\' or \'Mooring Operation\'. On selection of \'Mooring Operation\', the system shows another dropdown below to select the name of the Operation. \n\r\n\rj)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Reason: Dropdown to select from various available options.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.3.7 ROPE TAIL DISCARD","topics\\4.3.7_ROPE_TAIL_DISCARD.htm","ROPE TAIL DISPOSAL\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Rope Tail &gt; Rope Tail Disposal\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rRope Tail Disposal : Click on the \'Add Rope Tail Disposal\' button to make an entry of Rope Tail Disposal operation, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select Rope Tail: Dropdown to select the available rope tails as per their certificate numbers. \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date Out of Service: View only field\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Disposal Port Name: Text field to add name of Port where the rope tail was disposed.\n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reception Facility Name: Text field to add facility name which received the disposed rope tail in the Port. \n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Disposal Date: Calendar to select date of disposal. \n\r\n\r","4.3.8 ROPE TAIL DISPOSAL","topics\\4.3.8_ROPE_TAIL_DISPOSAL.htm","Mooring&nbsp;Rope Tail\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; See Sub sections for Details \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.3 MOORING ROPE TAIL","topics\\4.3_MOORING_ROPE_TAIL.htm","LOOSE EQUIPMENT INSPECTION&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis option is available to list and create Mooring loose equipment inspection details. All past inspections are listed on this page.\n\r\n\rTo view any past year data, click on the Year dropdown and press \'Search\' button besides to list past year data. By default               the current year dropdown is selected.\n\r\n\r                    &nbsp;\n\r\n\r                    \n\r\n\r&nbsp;New Inspection:         Click on this button to add a new inspection of Loose Equipment.&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\r\n\rMooring Loose Equipment Inspection View -                     \n\r\n\rThis page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Loose Equipment &gt; Loose Equipment Inspection &gt; Add&nbsp;LE Inspection option. ( As per the Required Equipment)\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rThe options on this page are listed below with respective details - \n\r\n\rInspection By: Generally Name &amp; Rank of the person inspecting to be inserted here.\n\r\n\rInspection Date: Calendar to choose the actual date when the selected loose equipment were inspected. \n\r\n\rLoose Equipment Type: Dropdown list to select from the list of Loose equipment. \n\r\n\rOn choosing the loose equipment type, the page will display all available loose equipment onboard, following options are available to fill after that - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Equipment Type: View only field (as selected equipment type). \n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Number: View only field - Identification / Certificate number of the equipment as inserted when added in the Loose Equipment Details form. \n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Condition: Dropdown to choose from \'Excellent\' or \'Good\' or \'Acceptable\' or \'Not Acceptable\'. \n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Remarks: Text Box to insert remarks, if any. \n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Photo 1 &amp; 2: Non Compulsory Option to insert photographs for each loose equipment during inspection. \n\r\n\r          &nbsp; \n\r\n\rDownload Inspection Excel Sheet: Click this button to download an automatically generated excel sheet containing all available loose equipment onboard. This can be printed and carried along during inspection for ease of use. \n\r\n\rSave: After inserting Inspection data, click on Save button to Save. If Save is not clicked, data will not be saved. \n\r\n\rCancel: Click on this button if the user does not want to save the inserted data. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.4.1 LOOSE EQUIPMENT INSPECTION","topics\\4.4.1_LOOSE_EQUIPMENT_INSPECTION.htm","LOOSE EQUIPMENT DETAILS \n\r\n\rAll Loose Equipment details shall be listed in this section. \n\r\n\r          \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; To add&nbsp;new Loose Equipment detail, click on \'Add Loose Equipment\' button on top right side under the various type of Loose Equipment.(Shown in the RED Box)&nbsp; \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rLoose Equipment Details Form View - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Loose Equipment &gt; Loose Equipment Details&gt; Add Loose Equipment.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Joining Shackle - Fields in the form are as below - \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rIdentification number: Insert embedded no or Ship\'s own identification number assigned\n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Text field\n\r\n\rMBL (T): Maximum breaking load in tonnes\n\r\n\rType: Dropdown to select one value\n\r\n\rCertificate Number: Number as per available certificate\n\r\n\rReceived Date: Calendar to insert date of receipt of that equipment\n\r\n\rInstalled Date: Calendar to insert date when equipment was put in service. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Messenger Rope - Fields in the form are as below - \n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Text field\n\r\n\rRope Construction: Text field to enter rope construction details. \n\r\n\rDiameter (mm) : Enter rope diameter here in millimetres.\n\r\n\rLength (mtrs) : Enter rope length here in metres.\n\r\n\rMBL (T) : Enter rope MBL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rLDBF (T) : Enter rope LDBF here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rWLL (T) : Enter rope WLL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rCertificate Number: Enter the Rope Certificate Number here. \n\r\n\rReceived Date: Compulsory field, Calendar to select date of receipt of the rope. This date can only be a past date. \n\r\n\rInstalled Date: Non-compulsory field, Calendar to select the installation date. In case the rope is kept as non-used spare, please leave this field blank. \n\r\n\rThis field is connected to calculation of discard criteria, hence only apply when the rope is in actual use. \n\r\n\rRope Tagging: Dropdown to select Yes / No. Ropes are ge\n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter remarks related to the rope. \n\r\n\rSave: Press Save button to save all data entered. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rc)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rope Stopper - Fields in the form are as below - \n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Text field\n\r\n\rRope Construction: Text field to enter rope construction details. \n\r\n\rDiameter (mm) : Enter rope diameter here in millimetres.\n\r\n\rLength (mtrs) : Enter rope length here in metres.\n\r\n\rMBL (T) : Enter rope MBL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rLDBF (T) : Enter rope LDBF here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rWLL (T) : Enter rope WLL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rCertificate Number: Enter the Rope Certificate Number here. \n\r\n\rReceived Date: Compulsory field, Calendar to select date of receipt of the rope. This date can only be a past date. \n\r\n\rInstalled Date: Non-compulsory field, Calendar to select the installation date. In case the rope is kept as non-used spare, please leave this field blank. \n\r\n\rThis field is connected to calculation of discard criteria, hence only apply when the rope is in actual use. \n\r\n\rRope Tagging: Dropdown to select Yes / No. Ropes are ge\n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter remarks related to the rope. \n\r\n\rSave: Press Save button to save all data entered. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rd)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Chain Stopper - Fields in the form are as below - \n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Text field\n\r\n\rCertificate Number: Enter the Rope Certificate Number here. \n\r\n\rMBL (T) : Enter rope MBL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rLength: Length in metres\n\r\n\rReceived Date: Compulsory field, Calendar to select date of receipt of the rope. This date can only be a past date. \n\r\n\rInstalled Date: Non-compulsory field, Calendar to select the installation date. In case the rope is kept as non-used spare, please leave this field blank. \n\r\n\rThis field is connected to calculation of discard criteria, hence only apply when the rope is in actual use. \n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter remarks related to the rope. \n\r\n\rSave: Press Save button to save all data entered. \n\r\n\re)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fire Wire - Fields in the form are as below - \n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Text field\n\r\n\rRope Construction: Text field to enter rope construction details. \n\r\n\rDiameter (mm) : Enter rope diameter here in millimetres.\n\r\n\rLength (mtrs) : Enter rope length here in metres.\n\r\n\rMBL (T) : Enter rope MBL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rLDBF (T) : Enter rope LDBF here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rWLL (T) : Enter rope WLL here in Tonnes. \n\r\n\rCertificate Number: Enter the Rope Certificate Number here. \n\r\n\rReceived Date: Compulsory field, Calendar to select date of receipt of the rope. This date can only be a past date. \n\r\n\rInstalled Date: Non-compulsory field, Calendar to select the installation date. In case the rope is kept as non-used spare, please leave this field blank. \n\r\n\rThis field is connected to calculation of discard criteria, hence only apply when the rope is in actual use. \n\r\n\rRope Tagging: Dropdown to select Yes / No. Ropes are ge\n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter remarks related to the rope. \n\r\n\rSave: Press Save button to save all data entered. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rf)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Chafe Guard - Fields in the form are as below - \n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Text field\n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter remarks related to the rope. \n\r\n\rSave: Press Save button to save all data entered. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rg)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Winch Brake Test Kit - Fields in the form are as below - \n\r\n\rManufacturer Name: Text field\n\r\n\rRemarks: Text box to enter remarks related to the rope. \n\r\n\rSave: Press Save button to save all data entered. ","4.4.2 LOOSE EQUIPMENT DETAILS","topics\\4.4.2_LOOSE_EQUIPMENT_DETAILS.htm","LOOSE EQUIPMENT DAMAGE\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Loose Equipment &gt; Loose Equipment Damage\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rLoose Equipment Damage :                        \n\r  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Select Equipment Type:&nbsp;S  elect the Tab available loose equipment types.\n\r  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click on the     \'Add Loose Eq Damage\' button to make an entry of Loose Equipment Damage operation.\n\r  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Certificate No. : Dropdown populates after selection of Loose equipment type. All Loose equipment associated with a particular type will be available here.&nbsp;        \n\r  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Observed: Dropdown to select the operation when damage was located i.e. during \'Inspection\' or \'Mooring operation\'. \n\r  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Damage Date: Calendar to select date of damage observed. \n\r  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reason Observed: Dropdown to select \'Yes\' or \'No\'. Select \'Yes\' if the damage resulted in an incident and report of incident is recorded. \n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.4.3 LOOSE EQUIPMENT DAMAGE","topics\\4.4.3_LOOSE_EQUIPMENT_DAMAGE.htm","LOOSE EQUIPMENT DISCARD\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Loose Equipment &gt; Loose Equipment Discard\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rLoose Equipment Discard : \n\r\n\r \n\r   Select Equipment Type:&nbsp;Select the TAB&nbsp;available for different&nbsp;loose equipment types.\n\r   Click on the \'Add Loose Equipment Discard\' button to make an entry of Loose Equipment Discard operation, which shall open the form. \n\r   Certificate No. : Dropdown populates after selection of Loose equipment type. All Loose equipment associated with a particular type will be available here.&nbsp; \n\r                      Date Out of Service: Calendar to select date of Discard or Out of Service\n\r  Reason Out of Service: Dropdown to select reason for discard.&nbsp;\n\r  &nbsp;Damage Observed: Dropdown to select from options of \'Inspection\' or \'Mooring Operation\'. On selection of \'Mooring Operation\', the system shows another dropdown below to select the name of the Operation. \n\r","4.4.4 LOOSE EQUIPMENT DISCARD","topics\\4.4.4_LOOSE_EQUIPMENT_DISCARD.htm","LOOSE EQUIPMENT DISPOSAL\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Loose Equipment &gt; Loose Equipment Disposal\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rLoose Equipment Disposal : \n\r\n\r\n\r  Select Equipment Type: Select &nbsp;the TAB for&nbsp;available   loose equipment types.\n\r  Click on the \'Add Loose Equipment Disposal\' button to   make an entry of Loose Equipment Disposal operation. \n\r  Choose Equipment: Dropdown populates after selection of Loose   equipment type. All Loose equipment associated with a particular type will be   available here.&nbsp; \n\r  Date Out of Service:   Calendar to select date of Discard or Out of Service\n\r  Disposal Port Name: Text field to add name of Port where the rope   tail was disposed.\n\r  Reception Facility Name: Text field to add facility name which   received the disposed rope tail in the Port. \n\r  Disposal Date: Calendar to select date of disposal. \n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.4.5 LOOSE EQUIPMENT DISPOSAL","topics\\4.4.5_LOOSE_EQUIPMENT_DISPOSAL.htm","Mooring Loose Equipment&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; See Sub sections for Details \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.4 MOORING LOOSE EQUIPMENT","topics\\4.4_MOORING_LOOSE_EQUIPMENT.htm","MOORING WINCH\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Mooring Winch.\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThis displays the nomenclature for the Mooring Winches. It is a fixed list to choose from. Any amendments to this list shall be requested from our support team on approval from your Company.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.5 MOORING WINCH","topics\\4.5_MOORING_WINCH.htm","LINE STATUS\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt;&nbsp;Line Status\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rThis section lists the complete status of each&nbsp;Line in following subsections - \n\r\n\r&nbsp; \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Active Records : Lists ropes which are currently in use and not \'Discarded\'. \n\r\n\rTo check&nbsp;Line details, click on \'Line Details\' link which will open the page to list all details of the&nbsp;line in its lifecycle. \n\r\n\rThis list also displays the Current Running hours and next inspection due date. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Past Records: Lists ropes which are already \'Discarded\'. \n\r\n\rTo check&nbsp;line details, click on \'Line Details\' link which will open the page to list all details of the&nbsp;Line in its lifecycle. ","4.6 LINE STATUS","topics\\4.6_LINE_STATUS.htm","ROPE TAIL STATUS\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt; Rope Tail Status\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rThis section lists the complete status of each Rope Tail, in following subsections - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Active Records : Lists rope tails which are currently in use and not \'Discarded\'. \n\r\n\rTo check rope tail details, click on \'Rope Tail Details\' link which will open the page to list all details of the rope in its lifecycle. \n\r\n\rThis list also displays the Current Running hours and next inspection due date. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rb)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Past Records: Lists ropes which are already \'Discarded\'. \n\r\n\rTo check rope tail details, click on \'Rope Tail Details\' link which will open the page to list all details of the rope in its lifecycle. ","4.7 ROPE TAIL STATUS","topics\\4.7_ROPE_TAIL_STATUS.htm","INSPECTION DISCARD CRITERIA\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rThe System consist of the Administration added Criteria for&nbsp;Inspection of the Line, Tails, Loose Equipment&nbsp;and Winch Rotation settinga) Mooring Lines and Mooring Rope Tails\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;b) Loose Equipment\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;c) Winch Rotation \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r&nbsp;","4.8 INSPECTION DISCARD CRITERIA","topics\\4.8_INSPECTION_DISCARD_CRITERIA.htm","&nbsp;LINE RESIDUAL LAB TEST\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This page appears from LMPR &gt;&nbsp;Line Residual Lab Test\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\rTo add the&nbsp;Line Residual Strength Test report, which you have received form the testing laboratory, please follow below steps - \n\r\n\ra)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click on \'Add&nbsp;Line Res Strength Test\' button to make an entry, which shall open the form. Form fields are explained as below -\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Select Line: Dropdown lists&nbsp;Line Certificate numbers to be selected as desired\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Line&nbsp;Type: View only field, automatically populates on selection of Select&nbsp;Line field. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manufacturer: View only field, automatically populates on selection of Select&nbsp;Line field. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Line&nbsp;Location: View only field, automatically populates on selection of Select&nbsp;Line field.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lab Test Date: Select the Lab test date as mentioned in the lab testing report. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Months in Service: View only field, displayed in units as \'Months\', calculated as (Lab Test Date - Installed Date).\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Running Hours in Service: View only field, Current running hours as being recorded automatically. &nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Residual Strength as per Test Report (Percentage): Enter percentage as mentioned in the lab test report (Max 100%). \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Remarks: Text box to enter your remarks, if any.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reset: Pressing this button resets the form entries you made, after reset, reselect the&nbsp;Line to fill the form again.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Save: After entering all information in the form, click on Save button to save in records. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cancel: Pressing this button will take you back to the list.&nbsp; \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r","4.9 LINE RESIDUAL LAB TEST","topics\\4.9_LINE_RESIDUAL_LAB_TEST.htm","TRAINING CONTENT\n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\rThe training module is to host training content pertaining to mooring. The training content may be provided by your Company or even the Vessel can upload their own content.","5.0 TRAINING CONTENT","topics\\5.0_TRAINING_CONTENT.htm","Types of Files allowed to be uploaded      &nbsp;      \n\r  Video files  Image files  PDF Files  MS Excel files  MS Word files\n\r  &nbsp;","5.1 TYPES OF FILES ALLOWED TO BE UPLOADED","topics\\5.1_TYPES_OF_FILES_ALLOWED_TO_BE_UPLOADED.htm","Using Training Content module&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n\r\n\rThe features of the Training content screen may be used as following : \n\r\n\r&nbsp;\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; i.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Add Attachment: To add any training content file. Procedure to add a file is explained in 7.3 of this manual. \n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ii.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; View : To view the training content, depending on the content uploaded, it will open the respective appliction from your computer to display the content, eg: for Video files, it will open your default media player, for pdf files, it will open the default pdf viewer etc.\n\r\n\r&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; iii.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scrolling Pages: For large number of entries in the list, system divides it to various pages. To scroll the pages, use the toggle arrows. Single arrow is for next / previous page, double arrows is for last or first page as per the direction of the arrow. ","5.2 USING TRAINING CONTENT MODULE","topics\\5.2_USING_TRAINING_CONTENT_MODULE.htm","Adding Training Content&nbsp;&nbsp;To add training content, follow below steps (screenshots below the steps): a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Click on \'Add Attachment\' button which opens a popup. b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the popup, enter \'File Name\' which will be displayed in the list after adding. c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now click on \'Browse\' button to browse the desired file from your computer. d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; At the time of browsing, you can change the file type extension from the dropdown given in the browse screen of your computer, to select desired file type. e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; After choosing the file, click on \'Open\' in the browse screen. f)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The file path will be displayed in the pop-up next to browse button. g)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now press \'Save\' from the poup to save the Training content. After saving, click on View and verify if file is opening correctly.","5.3 ADDING TRAINING CONTENT","topics\\5.3_ADDING_TRAINING_CONTENT.htm");